The paper deals with the problem of decentralized detection in wireless sensor networks, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the optimal rate allocation strategies for this scenario, which involves information theory and optimization (cs.IT), and the fusion center's decision-making process, which involves control and systems engineering (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the design of wireless sensor networks, which involves networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and the use of Gaussian observation models, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
